research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"jumprelu looks promising enough to deserve a family-specific stabilization pass, and its current default threshold initialization is likely too weak to realize the benefit of learned gating. Test jumprelu at K=128 with Adam using a higher initial threshold and smoother STE bandwidth so the encoder starts from a more selective regime.","summary":"The first jumprelu proxy was slightly better than the recent hybrid proxy points, but not strong enough to justify an immediate full run. This round keeps the new family and optimizer fixed and tunes its threshold dynamics directly, which is the most important family-specific lever for quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the right follow-up because JumpReLU's distinctive mechanism is its learned thresholding, so the defaults deserve at least one targeted pass before judging the family. The chosen threshold and bandwidth may still be off, but the hypothesis is clean and easy to evaluate.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.01"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["jumprelu at K=128/ef8/adam reached proxy FVU 0.2749013416469097, which is modestly competitive with recent hybrid proxy points but not yet enough for promotion.","Round 12 performs the first family-specific jumprelu stabilization pass by increasing the initial threshold and STE bandwidth to encourage more meaningful learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If stabilized jumprelu materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full before spending more rounds on hybrid variants.","If stabilized jumprelu is flat or worse, keep hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 as mainline and either try another new family or return to a training-dynamics experiment on the hybrid checkpoint."]}
research/history_archive/06_20260320_183226/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The round-1 crash was a startup-latency issue rather than a verdict on K=128 TopK quality; the most likely blocker is heavy launch overhead from compiling all transformer layers before the first step, so disabling compile and reducing preprocessing worker fanout should get a clean proxy measurement.","summary":"Retry the K=128 TopK Adam anchor as a proxy, but switch off model compilation and lower dataset preprocessing parallelism so the run can reach first metrics before the watchdog fires.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"run_stability","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This does not improve quality directly and may leave some steady-state throughput on the table. If the run still times out before first metrics, the real bottleneck is likely elsewhere in startup rather than compile overhead.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3e-4"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"},{"key":"DATA_PREPROCESSING_NUM_PROC","value":"8"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 1 produced a first_step_timeout crash before any quality signal, so do not draw a negative conclusion about Adam or TopK from it.","Treat this as a startup/perf unblock attempt to recover a trustworthy K=128 anchor measurement."],"next_hypotheses":["If the retry runs and improves FVU, continue K=128 quality work before considering any lower-K point.","If the retry runs but quality remains weak, escalate to a new encoder family rather than continuing optimizer-local search.","If first_step_timeout persists even with compile disabled, investigate startup bottlenecks in sparsify/ for model loading, hook registration, or dataloader setup."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0015.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent new families have all clustered far above the current hybrid full frontier, so the most credible next move is a training-dynamics pass on the one family that has actually improved full FVU. Adding a modest orthogonality penalty to hybrid_topk may reduce decoder interference between active features, sharpen the effective support at K=128, and improve reconstruction quality without changing the proven architecture.","summary":"Adaptive-threshold TopK matched the jumprelu-level proxy plateau rather than breaking through, so architecture exploration has not yet produced a stronger mainline candidate. This round returns to the best-known hybrid_topk K=128/ef=8/Adam setup and tests a single quality-focused regularization change, using proxy first to see whether reduced decoder interference can move FVU meaningfully below the recent 0.27 proxy band.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a narrow follow-up on the only family with a verified full win, not another broad sweep. The risk is that orthogonality regularization could trade away too much fitting capacity, but it is a clean way to test whether the remaining bottleneck is feature interference rather than encoder expressivity.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"ORTHO_LAMBDA","value":"1e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Adaptive_threshold_topk did not improve beyond the recent jumprelu-level proxy plateau, so support-suppression alone is not enough to beat the current hybrid mainline.","Round 15 returns to hybrid_topk for a training-dynamics probe, testing whether mild decoder orthogonality regularization can improve K=128 quality by reducing active-feature interference."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk with ortho regularization improves proxy FVU materially, promote it to full as the next mainline quality test.","If the ortho pass is flat or worse, bias the next round toward a more expressive new architecture edit rather than more local regularization sweeps."]}
