t-quality bet.","The EF=1 `topk` K ladder has shown consistent FVU improvement from K=96 to K=128 to K=192 without any compatibility risk; an untested midpoint K=160 is the cleanest next `<0.5x` frontier probe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `topk` K=160 lands near the expected ~0.18 FVU at ~0.41x, test `K=176` next to refine the mid-right edge of the `<0.5x` frontier.","If `topk` K=160 underperforms the monotone trend, shift the next round to a different directly compatible low-cost selector family instead of continuing dense K sweeps.","If runtime regresses disproportionately at K=160, treat that as a system-side warning and prefer lower-cost frontier densification over larger-K topk pushes."],"reference_round":242}
